In Java, catch blocks must be ordered from most specific to most general
Child exceptions first then Parent exceptions later

example:
try
{
    // risky code
} 
catch (NullPointerException e) 
{
    System.out.println("Null pointer exception");
} 
catch (ArithmeticException e) 
{
    System.out.println("Arithmetic exception");
} 
catch (Exception e) 
{
    System.out.println("General exception");
}


Exception is the parent of all exceptions
Catch specific problems first, general problems last